BARIADI District residents will now easily access telecommunication services including bio-metric SIM card registrations. This comes following the launch of the new Tigo shop in the district which is in line with the company’s strategy to improve service delivery to customers. Speaking during the launch on Thursday, District Commissioner (DC), Mr Festo Kiswaga commended company for its determination in investing its resources to ensure customers receive World-class services. “Customer services are often at the heart of business which aims to provide an exceptional service that leaves the customer feeling valued and respected,” Mr Kiswaga said. The DC said the launched shop will ensure that they no longer have to travel along way to get access telecom services. The company’s Lake Zone Director, Uthmaan Madati said the new shop features a special experience zone where customers can get the opportunity to test and experience different products.